🏗️ System Overview
The solution is a data-driven MQ topology transformation engine that ingests complex AS-IS configurations and produces a simplified, standardized, and constraint-compliant TARGET architecture.
🔧 High-Level Architecture
The system is structured as a pipeline of modular components, where each stage processes and enriches the data before passing it to the next stage.
⚙️ Major Components
1. 📥 Input Layer
Reads MQ configuration data from CSV files
Validates schema and normalizes fields
Treats the dataset as the single source of truth
2. 🔍 Flow Extraction Engine
Groups records into producer → consumer flows
Identifies:
Producer/Consumer apps
Home Queue Managers
Routing targets
Queue types (Local, Remote, Alias)
Builds a structured flow object model
3. 🧠 Analysis & Classification Engine
Evaluates each flow using:
QM-level matching
Queue-level matching
Cross-dataset evidence
Classifies flows into:
INDIRECT_COMPLETE
QM_ONLY_MATCH
QUEUE_ONLY_MATCH
MULTI_CANDIDATE
ORPHAN
Performs health checks and ambiguity detection
4. ⚙️ Optimization Decision Engine
Applies rule-based logic to determine:
Whether a flow should be included in target
Required transformation strategy
Supports:
Automatic decisions
Optional expert overrides
Marks flows as:
approved
needs_review
excluded
5. 🏗️ Target Topology Builder
Converts valid flows into canonical MQ design
Enforces constraints:
One QM per application
Producer writes locally
Consumer reads locally
Cross-QM routing via remote/XMIT/channels
Generates standardized MQ objects:
Local queues
Remote queues
Transmission queues
Channels
6. ✅ Validation Engine
Verifies target topology correctness:
Constraint compliance
No legacy QM leakage
Structural integrity
Flags violations before output generation
7. 📊 Comparison & Reporting Layer
Compares AS-IS vs TARGET:
Complexity reduction
Routing simplification
Generates:
Explanation report
Data quality report
Transformation summary
8. 📤 Output Layer
Produces automation-ready artifacts:
target_topology.csv
target_topology_input_schema.csv
.md reports for analysis and documentation
🔄 End-to-End Flow
Plain text
Input CSV
   ↓
Flow Extraction
   ↓
Analysis & Classification
   ↓
Optimization Decisions (Auto + Expert)
   ↓
Target Topology Builder
   ↓
Validation
   ↓
Comparison & Reports
   ↓
Final Output (CSV + Documentation)
🎯 Key Design Principles
Data-driven: No assumptions beyond input dataset
Explainable: Every decision is traceable and justified
Constraint-first: Target design strictly enforces MQ rules
Modular: Each component is independently testable
Extensible: Supports future AI-driven optimization
🚀 Summary
The system transforms fragmented MQ configurations into a clean, deterministic, and scalable architecture by combining structured data extraction, intelligent reasoning, and rule-based optimization.
